Summary:
Age: 56 years
Gender: Female
Cancer diagnosis: Stage II right breast cancer initially diagnosed in May 2013, now with metastatic relapse involving lungs, peritoneum, liver, and ovary, with local recurrence near the right axilla and implant.
PMH: Anxiety, hyperlipidemia
Prior cancer treatments: Mastectomy with sentinel node and implant reconstruction in June 2013. Declined adjuvant therapy and tamoxifen.
Current cancer treatments: Pending biopsy and further staging to guide treatment; discussed potential use of Ibrance if HR+/HER2- confirmed.
Current medication list: No current medications; patient takes a long list of supplements.
Summary of most recent oncology visit (12/30/2019): 56-year-old female with a history of Stage II right breast cancer, now presenting with metastatic relapse. She is scheduled for a biopsy of the right axilla and further staging. Treatment options discussed, focusing on palliative care to improve quality and length of life. Patient appears anxious but has good support from her husband.

Summary:
Age: 44 years
Gender: Female
Cancer diagnosis: Metastatic breast cancer, early stage endometrial cancer, colon cancer
PMH: Lynch Syndrome, anemia, peripheral neuropathy, anxiety, hot flashes, chronic headaches, hyponatremia, hypokalemia
Prior cancer treatments: Neoadjuvant therapy, partial mastectomy, adjuvant therapy, gemcitabine + carboplatin, Abraxane and Pembrolizumab
Current cancer treatments: Irinotecan started on 06/30/19, modified to every other week due to poor tolerance
Current medication list: Albuterol, Ambien CR, cyclobenzaprine, diphenoxylate-atropine, docusate sodium, gabapentin, lidocaine-prilocaine, loperamide, lorazepam, lurasidone, magnesium oxide, morphine, omeprazole, ondansetron, oxycodone, polyethylene glycol, pregabalin, prochlorperazine, rivaroxaban, simethicone, venlafaxine (discontinued), naloxone
Summary of most recent oncology visit: 44-year-old female with Lynch Syndrome, early stage endometrial and colon cancer, and newly diagnosed metastatic breast cancer. She is currently on cycle 3 day 1 of Irinotecan, modified due to side effects. She presents with increased chest wall tenderness, erythema, and edema, treated with Doxycycline. Experiencing worsening back pain, anemia treated with 1 unit pRBC, and peripheral neuropathy. MRI shows numerous bone marrow replacing lesions. Plans include re-evaluation for radiation therapy, monitoring of liver function and hepatitis B status, and follow-up in 2 weeks.

Summary:
Age: 53 years
Gender: Female
Cancer diagnosis: Stage IIA invasive ductal carcinoma (IDC) of the right breast, hormone receptor-positive (HR+), HER2-neu negative
PMH: Hyperlipidemia, pre-diabetes
Prior cancer treatments: None
Current cancer treatments: Discussed neoadjuvant therapy, chemotherapy, surgery, radiation, and hormonal blockade
Current medication list: None on file
Summary of most recent oncology visit (08/31/2021): 53-year-old female with newly diagnosed Stage IIA HR+ HER2-neu negative IDC of the right breast. Discussed treatment options including chemotherapy, surgery, radiation, and hormonal therapy to reduce risks of local and systemic recurrence. Genetic testing and PET CT are pending. Recommended lifestyle modifications for cancer risk reduction. No current medications. Good support system. Follow-up planned after pending tests. Consultation conducted via telehealth.
Family history: Leukemia in father, breast cancer in paternal and maternal aunts
Social history: Never smoker, no alcohol or drug use, single, no children
Allergies: No known allergies
Performance status: Asymptomatic (0)
Lifestyle: Occasionally walks, moderate sweet tooth, sleeps 5-6 hours, medium stress level
Physical exam: No acute distress, appears stated age, no vitals taken during this telehealth visit

Summary:
Age: 75 years
Gender: Female
Cancer diagnosis: ER+/PR+/HER2- left breast invasive ductal carcinoma
PMH: hypertension, hypercholesterolemia, allergic rhinitis, osteoporosis
Prior cancer treatments: Left mastectomy with SLN biopsy (completed on 10/29/2016)
Current cancer treatments: Letrozole (started 12/02/2016)
Current medication list: aspirin, calcium carbonate, cholecalciferol (vitamin D3), letrozole, loratadine, metoprolol succinate, metoprolol tartrate, pravastatin
Summary of most recent oncology visit: 75-year-old female with a history of left breast invasive ductal carcinoma, post-mastectomy, currently on Letrozole. No evidence of disease recurrence. She reports improvement in pain after physical therapy and uses non-pharmacological methods for muscle cramps and headaches. Advised to continue current treatment and follow-up in 6 months or sooner if symptoms worsen.

Summary:
Age: 31 years
Gender: Female
Cancer diagnosis: Stage III ER+/PR+ HER2- Invasive Ductal Carcinoma (IDC) of the left breast, now with biopsy-proven metastatic recurrence involving left cervical lymph node
PMH: None specified
Prior cancer treatments: Bilateral mastectomies, adjuvant chemotherapy with Adriamycin/cytoxan (stopped after 3 cycles due to severe side effects), anti-estrogen therapy (leuprolide, exemestane, tamoxifen)
Current cancer treatments: Leuprolide (started January 2019), anastrozole (started March 2019), palbociclib (started April 2019)
Current medication list: amlodipine, anastrozole, escitalopram, gabapentin, hydrochlorothiazide, ondansetron, palbociclib, potassium chloride, venlafaxine
Summary of most recent oncology visit (12/07/2019): 31-year-old premenopausal female with a history of Stage III ER+/PR+ HER2- IDC of the left breast, now presenting with metastatic recurrence. She is currently on leuprolide, anastrozole, and palbociclib, and tolerating the therapy well. Plans include continuation of current therapy, monthly labs coinciding with lupron injections, and restaging studies before the next visit. Referral to radiation oncology for symptomatic disease in her left neck and brachial plexus has been made.

Summary:
Age: 56 years
Gender: Female
Cancer diagnosis: Stage II right breast cancer initially diagnosed in May 2013, now presenting with metastatic relapse involving lungs, peritoneum, liver, and ovary, with regional recurrence near the right axilla and implant. Tumors originally 2.3 and 2.4 cm, node-negative, ER and PR positive, HER2 negative.
PMH: Anxiety, hyperlipidemia
Prior cancer treatments: Mastectomy with sentinel node and implant reconstruction in June 2013. Declined tamoxifen and did not receive radiation or chemotherapy.
Current cancer treatments: Pending tissue confirmation and staging workup. Planned treatment with Ibrance if biopsy confirms HR+/HER2-.
Current medication list: Long list of supplements (details not provided in the note)
Allergies: Penicillins (reaction: rash)
Summary of most recent oncology visit (12/30/2019): 56-year-old female with a history of Stage II right breast cancer s/p mastectomy, now presenting with metastatic relapse. She is scheduled for a biopsy of the right axilla and further staging workup. Discussed palliative treatment options to improve quality and length of life. Patient appears anxious with good support from her husband. No outpatient medications reported; takes various supplements.

Summary:
Age: 44 years
Gender: Female
Cancer diagnosis: Early stage endometrial and colon cancer, metastatic breast cancer
PMH: Lynch Syndrome
Prior cancer treatments: Neoadjuvant therapy, partial mastectomy, adjuvant chemotherapy, gemcitabine + carboplatin, Abraxane and Pembrolizumab
Current cancer treatments: Started Irinotecan on 06/30/19
Current medication list: Albuterol, Ambien CR, cyclobenzaprine, diphenoxylate-atropine, docusate sodium, gabapentin, lidocaine-prilocaine, loperamide, lorazepam, lurasidone, magnesium oxide, morphine, omeprazole, ondansetron, oxycodone, polyethylene glycol, pregabalin, prochlorperazine, rivaroxaban, simethicone, Effexor-XR (venlafaxine discontinued)
Summary of most recent oncology visit: 44-year-old female with Lynch Syndrome, early stage endometrial and colon cancer, and newly diagnosed metastatic breast cancer on Irinotecan. Reports multiple symptoms including confusion, chest pain, severe back pain, anxiety, and depression. Current treatment plan includes continuation of Irinotecan, management of pain and symptoms, and monitoring. MRI pending for further evaluation. Patient education and counseling provided during visit.

Summary:
Age: 53 years
Gender: Female
Cancer diagnosis: Stage IIA invasive ductal carcinoma (IDC) of the right breast, hormone receptor-positive, HER2-neu negative
PMH: Hyperlipidemia, pre-diabetes
Prior cancer treatments: None
Current cancer treatments: Under discussion (neoadjuvant therapy recommended)
Current medication list: None on file
Summary of most recent oncology visit (08/31/2021): 53-year-old female with newly diagnosed Stage IIA right IDC of the breast, node positive, HR+, HER2-neu negative. During the telehealth consultation, discussions on chemotherapy, surgery, radiation, and hormonal blockade were held to decrease the risk of both local and systemic recurrence. Lifestyle modifications were also recommended. Genetic testing and PET CT are pending. Follow-up planned after results are available.
Family history: Leukemia (father), breast cancer (paternal aunt at age 60, maternal aunt)
Social history: Never smoker, never alcohol, no drug use, single, no children
Allergies: No known allergies
Performance status: Asymptomatic (0)
Lifestyle: Occasional exercise, moderate sweet consumption, 5-6 hours of sleep with medication, medium stress levels with good support.

Age: 75 years  
Gender: Female  
Cancer diagnosis: ER+/PR+/HER2- left breast invasive ductal carcinoma  
PMH: hypertension, hypercholesterolemia, allergic rhinitis, osteoporosis  
Prior cancer treatments: Left mastectomy with sentinel lymph node biopsy (10/29/2016)  
Current cancer treatments: Letrozole since 12/02/2016  
Current medication list: Letrozole, aspirin, calcium carbonate, cholecalciferol (vitamin D3), loratadine, metoprolol succinate, metoprolol tartrate, pravastatin  
Summary of most recent oncology visit: 75-year-old female post-mastectomy for ER+/PR+/HER2- breast cancer, currently on Letrozole. She reports improved pain from physical therapy and no evidence of disease recurrence on recent imaging. Advised to continue Letrozole, annual mammograms, and monitor bone density. Current issues include muscle cramps, back and leg pain, and loose stools, with management plans in place for each. Follow-up in 6 months or as needed.

Summary:
Age: 31 years
Gender: Female
Cancer diagnosis: Stage III ER+/PR+/HER2- invasive ductal carcinoma (IDC) of the left breast, with metastatic recurrence involving left cervical lymph nodes and left brachial plexus
PMH: None specified
Prior cancer treatments: Bilateral breast skin-sparing mastectomy, adjuvant chemotherapy with Adriamycin/cyclophosphamide (stopped after 3 cycles due to adverse effects), anti-estrogen therapy (leuprolide, exemestane, tamoxifen)
Current cancer treatments: Leuprolide (since January 2019), anastrozole (since March 2019), palbociclib (since April 2019)
Current medication list: amlodipine, anastrozole, escitalopram, gabapentin, hydrochlorothiazide, ondansetron, palbociclib, potassium chloride, venlafaxine
Summary of most recent oncology visit (12/07/2019): 31-year-old premenopausal female with a history of stage III ER+/PR+/HER2- IDC of the left breast, now with biopsy-proven metastatic recurrence, currently on leuprolide, anastrozole, and palbociclib. She is symptomatic with neck pain and left arm symptoms due to brachial plexus involvement. She tolerates current therapy and will continue with planned restaging studies and monthly labs on the days of her lupron injections. Referrals to radiation oncology have been made for symptomatic management.

Summary:
Age: 56 years
Gender: Female
Cancer diagnosis: Stage II right breast cancer, initially discovered in 2013, now metastatic with spread to lungs, liver, peritoneum, and ovary.
PMH: Anxiety, hyperlipidemia.
Prior cancer treatments: Mastectomy with sentinel node biopsy and implant reconstruction in 2013, declined tamoxifen and no chemotherapy or radiation.
Current cancer treatments: Pending tissue confirmation, planning to start Ibrance if hormone receptor-positive upon reevaluation.
Current medication list: Patient reported taking a long list of supplements, specifics not on file.
Summary of most recent oncology visit (12/30/2019): 56-year-old female with a history of right breast cancer recently presenting with symptoms leading to the discovery of widespread metastatic disease. Comprehensive staging and biopsy scheduled to confirm tissue characteristics and plan treatment. Treatment to be palliative aimed at improving quality and length of life. Patient expressed fear and anxiety, supported by her husband at the visit. Referrals made for integrative medicine and a detailed planned follow-up after biopsy and staging results.
Allergies: Penicillins (rash).

Summary:
Age: 44 years
Gender: Female
Cancer diagnosis: Early-stage endometrial and colon cancer, metastatic breast cancer
PMH: Lynch syndrome, anemia due to malignancy and chemotherapy, peripheral neuropathy due to Abraxane, anxiety, hot flashes, chronic headaches, hyponatremia, hypokalemia, history of DVT
Prior cancer treatments: Neoadjuvant therapy and weekly cycles of carboplatin/paclitaxel (discontinued due to poor tolerance), partial mastectomy, adjuvant therapy, gemcitabine + carboplatin for pectoral lymph nodes, local recurrence treated with Doxycycline, recent start of Irinotecan
Current cancer treatments: Irinotecan (started 06/30/19, adjusted to every other week at 150mg/m² on days 1 and 15 every 28 days)
Current medication list: Albuterol, AMBIEN CR, cyclobenzaprine, diphenoxylate-atropine, docusate sodium, gabapentin, lidocaine-prilocaine, loperamide, lorazepam, lurasidone, magnesium oxide, morphine, omeprazole, ondansetron, oxycodone, polyethylene glycol, pregabalin, prochlorperazine, rivaroxaban, simethicone, venlafaxine (Effexor-XR)
Summary of most recent oncology visit: 44-year-old female with Lynch Syndrome, early-stage endometrial and colon cancer, and newly diagnosed metastatic breast cancer, currently on adjusted dose of Irinotecan. Recent issues with chest wall pain and erythema treated with antibiotics and complications of severe anemia managed with a blood transfusion. Reports symptoms of anxiety, chronic headaches, peripheral neuropathy, sacral pain, and hyponatremia, addressing with various supportive medications and modifications in chemotherapy dosing. Upcoming scans scheduled for September 2019. Will continue current management and follow-up in 2 weeks.

Age: 53 years
Gender: Female

PMH: Hyperlipidemia, pre-diabetes

Current cancer treatments: Discussed neoadjuvant chemotherapy, surgery, radiation, and hormonal therapy

Summary:
- Age: 75 years
- Gender: Female
- Cancer diagnosis: ER+/PR+/HER2- left breast invasive ductal carcinoma
- PMH: hypertension, hypercholesterolemia, allergic rhinitis, hepatitis A, cataract surgery, colonoscopy
- Prior cancer treatments: Left mastectomy with sentinel lymph node biopsy, Letrozole therapy since December 2016
- Current cancer treatments: Letrozole 2.5 mg daily (since 12/02/2016)
- Current medication list: aspirin 81 mg, calcium carbonate, vitamin D3 (cholecalciferol 1000 units), letrozol e, loratadine, metoprolol succinate, metoprolol tartrate, pravastatin
- Summary of most recent oncology visit (6 months ago): 75-year-old female with history of left breast invasive ductal carcinoma, post-mastectomy, currently on Letrozole with no evidence of disease recurrence. Experiencing improved muscle cramping, back and thigh pain from physical therapy. Advised on magnesium supplement, and continuation of physical therapy for muscle tightness. Bone density scan showing improvement in femur neck, osteopenia in lumbar spine and femur stable, advised continuation of calcium and vitamin D supplements. Regular monitoring with DEXA scans recommended. Additionally, intermittent headaches and loose stools post-meals managed with OTC medications and dietary adjustments, advised follow-up with primary care for headache management if persistent. Counseled on recognizing alarming signs and when to seek urgent care. Follow-up visit scheduled in 6 months or sooner for new or worsening symptoms.

Summary:
- Age: 31 years
- Gender: Female
- Cancer diagnosis: Recurrent metastatic invasive ductal carcinoma (IDC) of the left breast, Stage III, ER+/PR+/HER2-, with metastasis involving left cervical lymph node and left brachial plexus.
- PMH: Premenopausal status.
- Prior cancer treatments: Bilateral mastectomy with left axillary clearance, followed by adjuvant chemotherapy with Adriamycin and cyclophosphamide (stopped after 3 cycles due to severe side effects), anti-estrogen therapy (leuprolide, exemestane, tamoxifen).
- Current cancer treatments: Leuprolide (since January 2019), Anastrozole (since March 2019), Palbociclib (since April 2019).
- Current medication list: Amlodipine, Anastrozole, Escitalopram, Gabapentin, Hydrochlorothiazide, Ondansetron, Palbociclib, Potassium chloride, Venlafaxine.
- Summary of most recent oncology visit (12/07/2019): 31-year-old female with a history of recurrent, metastatic IDC of the left breast, now involving left cervical lymph nodes and left brachial plexus. Continues on hormonal therapy with leuprolide, anastrozole, and palbociclib, showing controlled disease but with new osseous metastasis suspected in the sternum. Patient has been referred to radiation oncology for brachial plexus involvement and plans are in place for restaging studies prior to the next visit. The patient tolerates current therapies with supportive medications and will continue with scheduled monthly labs.
